 Port Elizabeth police on Wednesday said that they are investigating a case of murder after the beheaded body of an unidentified man was found on Tuesday night. According to police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge, a passer-by discovered the beheaded body at about 9.30 pm close along the M19 close to Swartkops, Port Elizabeth. He said that the body had several stab wounds to the chest. “His head was also cut off by an unknown instrument or weapon,” Capt Beetge said. “The victim is estimated to be between the age of 20 to 30 years old." Captain Beetge said that the head of the man was found next to his body. “Anybody with information on his identity can contact Detective Warrant Officer Jacques Leonard on 082 847 4756.” Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. 